The paper discusses the use of neural networks for diagnostic rule extraction, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of minimal neural network architectures, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The application of the method in clinical research suggests a potential connection to computer engineering (cs.CE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
